Day 22 âœ”ï¸ Just two epiphanies that I would like to share. The first one is that, I didn't feel like doing yoga today; I just felt so sleepy and I almost convinced myself to go to bed. But then I remembered something. Often, there's been times where I've done things for people when I didn't feel like doing it, but I did it anyway because I was too weak to say "no."  I didn't feel like working out today, but I knew that I wouldn't regret it after. So why don't I say "yes" to myself, when I've willingly said to others in the past--and often regretted it?  Like many of us in the comment know, none of us ever regret a workout or yoga flow with you!

And the second thing I noticed was that I stopped talking negatively to myself when I was falling backwards or tripping or whatever--instead I started to reframe it as gratitude. Yoga is constantly showing me where my imbalances are, what I need to strengthen, and helping me to actually grow stronger than mind-body neurological connection. This also reminds me of life; that whenever I feel stupid from making a mistake or get humbled, that I am learning and getting stronger. 

My complacency is the cost of growing stronger, and to paraphrase Hemingway: some of us grow stronger from the places that we are broken. You are light teacher that helps us all not only nurture our weaknesses, but celebrate the flowers on our branches. Namaste ğŸŒğŸ™ğŸ’œ
